{"id":14881508,"mediaExerciseId":"443a32bd-7267-4cd4-a597-04073a50feb2","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"15","chapterTitle":"Raising Capital","groupId":612403,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":529,"solutions":[{"id":6020163,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to assess the IPO pricing. \n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The procedure of issuing shares of a private company to the market in the issuance of new stock is known as an **initial public offering (IPO)**. This enables a company to generate revenue from the general public.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The act of issuing an initial public offering (IPO) at a price less than its true market value on the public market is known as **underpricing**. Several variables influence the underpricing of new stocks.\n\nAs noted in the previous item, since this is Zipcar's first trade, the investment bank is genuinely concerned about receiving the security. The investment bank anticipates that share prices will increase to the level that shareholders believe is valuable. When a new offering is valued, investors may be ready to take a risk on it.Â \n\n**The firm has not made a profit, and the business model's viability has yet to be established.** This indicates that the feasibility of the business model, which is a critical factor in acquiring investment, is still unknown. It is challenging for the investment bank to price the assets in this circumstance.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"a57c90e6-d826-4ff1-9986-90164aee44ea","editorVersion":2,"